\newlabel{fig:covid_comparison}{{2}{26}{Disappearance of price elasticity during COVID-19. Pre-COVID elasticities are significantly negative (EU: $\EUPreIntB $\EUPreIntStars , EaP: $\EaPPreIntB $\EaPPreIntStars ), while COVID-era elasticities are statistically insignificant. Both shifts are significant at p$<$0.01. Error bars show 90\% confidence intervals; bars excluding zero correspond to p$<$0.10}{figure.2}{}}
